    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Crankcase, Crankshaft, Connecting
        Rods, And Pistons - Rear Cover
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Rear Cover</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid damage to the rear cover, make sure the rear oil seal is removed. Refer to "Rear Oil
                        Seal and Wear Sleeve" in this section.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1200718" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Rear Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel Pins</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear Cover Bolt Locations (8)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove rear cover mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently pry the rear cover away from crankcase, breaking the RTV sealant bond in the
                    process. Do not bend the rear cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
